<p>in understanding the bugle calls.  The mess hut was at the bottom of the two rows we occupied then, in Fovant Camp, &amp; Dingo soon found by the appeal from his stomach, which call brought the boys to this hut, here he was always fed.<br/>Thus he learned several calls, &amp; in particular the regimental call of the A.M.C.; All others having no interest for him.<br/>When the 16th went to Parkhouse camp, Dingo, who from a little short haired black ball, had grown to an awkward black pup, accompanied them.</p>
